are getting tougher.

101
00:04:20,030 --> 00:04:20,890
They're not as obedient

102
00:04:20,910 --> 00:04:21,690
as you guys used to be,

103
00:04:22,270 --> 00:04:22,770
though

104
00:04:23,880 --> 00:04:24,940
you weren't

105
00:04:25,030 --> 00:04:26,450
a rule-follower either.

106
00:04:27,270 --> 00:04:28,860
These young students
are bigger headaches than you.

107
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:29,810
Yet, I also spent

108
00:04:29,910 --> 00:04:31,250
much time worrying about you back then.

109
00:04:33,830 --> 00:04:35,570
Students are wayward in their own ways.

110
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:40,250
Mr. Fu, did you call me here

111
00:04:40,350 --> 00:04:41,250
just to take a walk

112
00:04:41,680 --> 00:04:42,370
down memory lane?

113
00:04:42,790 --> 00:04:43,540
Of course not.

114
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:45,980
Let's talk some real business.

115
00:04:46,830 --> 00:04:48,010
Have you made up your mind

116
00:04:48,030 --> 00:04:48,980
about giving that speech?

117
00:04:49,590 --> 00:04:51,420
Our school really needs

118
00:04:51,680 --> 00:04:53,660
a top grad like you

119
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:55,620
to come back and help your juniors.

120
00:04:55,790 --> 00:04:56,370
Tell them about

121
00:04:56,520 --> 00:04:57,860
your college experience

122
00:04:58,080 --> 00:04:58,770
at Capital University.

123
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:00,740
Give them some motivation

124
00:05:00,830 --> 00:05:01,660
and cheer them on.

125
00:05:02,350 --> 00:05:02,940
Now,

126
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:04,420
we need to push hard

127
00:05:04,710 --> 00:05:05,860
on both academics and mindset.

128
00:05:06,150 --> 00:05:06,810
Did you see

129
00:05:06,910 --> 00:05:07,980
that troublemaker earlier?

130
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:10,010
I suspended her on the spot.

131
00:05:10,270 --> 00:05:11,210
No one could talk me out of it.

132
00:05:14,910 --> 00:05:15,810
Anyway, enough about that.

133
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:17,860
How've things been
for you at school lately?

134
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:19,250
I got suspended, too.

135
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:23,130
Drink your tea.

136
00:05:24,470 --> 00:05:25,300
Not a single one of you is easy.

137
00:05:29,760 --> 00:05:30,540
Are you serious?

138
00:05:31,640 --> 00:05:32,250
Just drink.

139
00:05:37,270 --> 00:05:38,300
Gu Xuejiao, I'm heading off.

140
00:05:38,390 --> 00:05:38,740
Bye.

141
00:05:38,830 --> 00:05:39,210
Bye.

142
00:05:46,320 --> 00:05:47,450
No wonder Lin Zhihua

143
00:05:47,520 --> 00:05:48,620
likes writing code

144
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:49,210
during part-time gigs

145
00:05:49,640 --> 00:05:50,860
and memorizing vocab at work.

146
00:05:51,030 --> 00:05:51,890
It's so efficient.

147
00:05:52,960 --> 00:05:53,450
Hey, there,

148
00:05:53,590 --> 00:05:54,690
is this Class 8 of Grade 12?

149
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:55,100
Yes.

150
00:05:56,270 --> 00:05:58,370
Is Zhou Shiyun a homing pigeon?

151
00:05:58,560 --> 00:05:59,500
She informs parents in no time.

152
00:05:59,790 --> 00:06:00,690
Gu Xuejiao.

153
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:01,330
Mom.

154
00:06:01,520 --> 00:06:01,740
If…

155
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:02,890
If Zhou Shiyun's mom

156
00:06:02,910 --> 00:06:03,540
hadn't told you,

157
00:06:03,590 --> 00:06:04,420
you wouldn't even know

158
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:07,060
I caused such a mess at school.

159
00:06:08,270 --> 00:06:08,570
She…

160
00:06:09,520 --> 00:06:09,980
Mom,

161
00:06:10,440 --> 00:06:11,250
I swear

162
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:12,660
I didn't lay a finger on anyone.

163
00:06:13,150 --> 00:06:13,810
From beginning to end,

164
00:06:13,880 --> 00:06:15,100
the only thing I did was

165
00:06:15,350 --> 00:06:17,060
try to keep things from spiraling.

166
00:06:17,350 --> 00:06:18,210
If you didn't touch anyone,

167
00:06:18,350 --> 00:06:19,450
why didn't you tell us?

168
00:06:19,520 --> 00:06:20,890
Why hide it from us?

169
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:21,770
Because I knew that

170
00:06:21,830 --> 00:06:22,570
even if I told you

171
00:06:22,710 --> 00:06:23,420
I didn't hurt anyone,

172
00:06:23,710 --> 00:06:24,740
you'd still drag me

173
00:06:24,830 --> 00:06:25,330
to apologize

174
00:06:25,440 --> 00:06:26,250
like you're doing now.

175
00:06:26,560 --> 00:06:27,130
You'd think that

176
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:28,420
saying sorry would smooth things over.

177
00:06:30,390 --> 00:06:32,420
It doesn't matter whose fault it is.

178
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:33,980
You should go and offer

179
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:34,810
an apology.

180
00:06:35,080 --> 00:06:35,450
Understand?

181
00:06:35,710 --> 00:06:37,570
A smile can disarm aggression.

182
00:06:38,440 --> 00:06:39,690
Just humble yourself

183
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:40,690
a little.

184
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:41,980
It never hurts.

185
00:06:44,230 --> 00:06:44,660
Mom,

186
00:06:45,150 --> 00:06:46,770
how humble should I be?

187
00:06:47,350 --> 00:06:48,620
Am I supposed to swallow my pride

188
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:50,370
and apologize to others

189
00:06:50,880 --> 00:06:51,770
for something I didn't do?

190
00:06:52,560 --> 00:06:53,130
And what

191
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:54,370
do we get out of that?

192
00:06:55,230 --> 00:06:56,570
Expired drinks we can't even finish?

193
00:06:57,440 --> 00:06:57,940
Xuejiao,

194
00:06:58,200 --> 00:06:59,180
here, have a drink.

195
00:06:59,590 --> 00:07:00,370
Why aren't you drinking?

196
00:07:00,880 --> 00:07:02,100
She loves this.

197
00:07:03,790 --> 00:07:05,330
But it's expired.

198
00:07:10,150 --> 00:07:11,570
Or maybe their snobbish attitude?

199
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:13,690
Can you get her a job?

200
00:07:14,350 --> 00:07:15,370
Any department.

201
00:07:15,830 --> 00:07:16,620
Let her do some

202
00:07:16,790 --> 00:07:17,330
odds and ends.

203
00:07:17,470 --> 00:07:20,100
My husband's company runs a tight ship.

204
00:07:20,520 --> 00:07:21,450
We may

205
00:07:21,960 --> 00:07:22,690
address

206
00:07:23,120 --> 00:07:24,540
each other as relatives,

207
00:07:25,080 --> 00:07:26,330
but we're not related by blood.

208
00:07:26,470 --> 00:07:27,370
I'm afraid

209
00:07:27,520 --> 00:07:28,860
there's really nothing
my husband can do.

210
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:30,180
Hope you understand.

211
00:07:33,440 --> 00:07:34,060
Xuejiao,

212
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:35,370
what's gotten into you?

213
00:07:35,590 --> 00:07:36,210
If you keep this up,

214
00:07:36,320 --> 00:07:37,180
how are you supposed to get along

215
00:07:37,270 --> 00:07:38,100
with your classmates?

216
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:39,060
I'm…

217
00:07:39,230 --> 00:07:40,570
I'm doing this for your own good.

218
00:07:40,830 --> 00:07:41,620
I don't need it.

219
00:07:42,230 --> 00:07:42,660
Mom,

220
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:47,100
